  "text": "Standard abdominal/pelvis ultrasound scanning was performed with a convex 2.4-5-MHz/transvaginal 5-9-MHz probe with the patient in the supine and gynecological positions, respectively, according to methodology and terminology described elsewhere [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Liver and spleen parenchyma, surface, hepatic and splenic hilum, upper abdomen, diaphragm, and peritoneum were scanned with both transabdominal and intercostal upper abdomen ultrasonography.",
